HEADWORD: Neo-Kantianism
<hw>Ne`o-Kant"i*an*ism</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The philosophy of modern
thinkers who follow <person>Kant</person> in his general theory of
knowledge, esp. of a group of German philosophers including <person>F.
A. Lange</person>, <person>H. Cohen</person>, <person>Paul
Natorp</person>, and others.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Neo-Lamarckism</ent>⟦br⟧
